HEADWORD: Abranchiata
<hw>A*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/, pl., the gills of
fishes.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of annelids, so called
because the species composing it have no special organs of
respiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

